## Response Management Pattern

This section operationalizes Requirement 1 (response management) and Requirement 2 (error recovery) from `04.03-production-readiness-patterns.md`.

Every agent MUST include a Response Management section referencing the production readiness patterns:

```markdown
## Response Management

**📖 Patterns:** [04.03-production-readiness-patterns.md](04.03-production-readiness-patterns.md)
```

After the reference, list 2–4 agent-specific scenarios with their expected responses. Use the format:

```markdown
- **[Trigger condition]** → "[Response message or action]"
```

Use these shared templates when authoring or validating the section:

- **📖 Agent response scaffold:** [agent.template.md](../../../.github/templates/00.00-prompt-engineering/agent.template.md)
- **📖 Error-recovery workflow template:** [output-guidance-validation-phases.template.md](../../../.github/templates/00.00-prompt-engineering/output-guidance-validation-phases.template.md)

---

## Test Scenario Structure

Every agent MUST include an embedded test scenario section. Use this structure:

```markdown
## Test Scenarios

| # | Scenario | Expected Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | [Happy path] | [Full workflow → expected outcome] |
| 2 | [Common variation] | [Adjusted workflow → expected outcome] |
| 3 | [Error/edge case] | [Error handling → expected outcome] |
```

Include 3–5 scenarios per agent. Scenarios MUST cover: happy path, a common variation, and at least one error/edge case.

---

## Boundary Section Template

Every agent MUST include three boundary tiers with minimum items (📖 see `01.06-system-parameters.md`):

| Tier | Emoji | Minimum items |
|---|---|---|
| Always Do | ✅ | 3 |
| Ask First | ⚠️ | 1 |
| Never Do | 🚫 | 2 |

**Structure:**
```markdown
## 🚨 CRITICAL BOUNDARIES

### ✅ Always Do
- [Agent-specific items]
- **📖 Output minimization rules**: [02.04-agent-shared-patterns.md](02.04-agent-shared-patterns.md) → Output Minimization Rules

### ⚠️ Ask First
- [Agent-specific items]

### 🚫 Never Do
- [Agent-specific items]
```

